title: French senator accused of drugging colleague will resign next month
subhed: Senator Joël Guerriau is facing trial for allegedly using ecstasy to spike National Assembly Deputy Sandrine Josso's drink, with the intention of sexually assaulting her. Guerriau denies the charges, describing the incident as a 'handling error.' Josso said the news of Guerriau's resignation had left her in 'disgust': 'This is not an act of responsibility or decency. It's a strategic retreat.'

title: The silent and destructive spread of laughing gas: 'That shit took my whole life'
subhed: A boy barely out of his teens, a man not yet 30, a young nursing assistant, a father: All share how their lives have been shattered by nitrous oxide. This legal, inexpensive and easily accessible substance has become a widely consumed and addictive drug.
